# Battlesmith
# Ability Name			Unique Key							Category of Ability		Type													Define					Description																																																																																																			Combat bonus											Weapon prof. bonus				Source Page		Aspects
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Battlesmith ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality										DESC:Battlesmiths gain no proficiency with any weapon or armor.																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.98
One with the Hammer		KEY:Battlesmith ~ One with the Hammer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:A battlesmith's long hours at the forge grant her a special bond with a hammer. When wielding a warhammer that she has crafted herself, a battlesmith adds her Wisdom bonus as a bonus to the damage dealt by the weapon.																																																																												BONUS:WEAPONPROF=Warhammer|DAMAGE|WIS	SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Secrets of the Forge		KEY:Battlesmith ~ Secrets of the Forge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:A battlesmith learns some of the great dwarven secrets of forging weapons and armor. A battlesmith receives Craft Magic Arms and Armor as a bonus feat, regardless of her caster level. Multiply the battle smith's class level by 3 to determine her effective caster level for the purpose of creating magic arms and armor (this benefit stacks with any other caster levels the battlesmith might have). The battlesmith must still meet any other prerequisites for the item's creation. This stipulation might mean that she needs the assistance of other characters to complete the creation of an item.																					SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Flesh of My Flesh			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Flesh of My Flesh			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DEFINE:FleshOfMyFleshACBonus|0	DESC:No armor fits so well as that created by a battlesmith for her own use. When wearing heavy armor that she has crafted herself, a battlesmith of 2nd level or higher gains a +1 sacred bonus to Armor Class. This bonus increases to +2 at 4th level.																																																											BONUS:COMBAT|AC|FleshOfMyFleshACBonus|TYPE=Sacred|PREEQUIP:1,Armor.Heavy								SOURCEPAGE:p.98	ASPECT:NAME|Flesh of My Flesh +%1|FleshOfMyFleshACBonus
Forged in Fire			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Forged in Fire			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:At 3rd level, a battlesmith becomes inured to the effects of fatigue and exhaustion, and can ignore their effects for a number of hours equal to her class level. At the end of this time, if the condition remains, the battlesmith succumbs to the effects.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Tempered in Blood			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Tempered in Blood			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:Once per day, a 5th-level battlesmith can attempt to resist the damage from a single blow. The battlesmith can attempt a Fortitude save (DC 10 + damage dealt) when struck and damaged by a melee attack with a weapon or natural attack (but not by a spell or other effect). If the save succeeds, the battlesmith takes only half damage from the blow; if it fails, she takes normal damage. The battlesmith must be aware of the attack and able to react to it to use this ability. If she is denied her Dexterity bonus to AC, she can't use this ability.																													SOURCEPAGE:p.98



###Block: Substitution Levels
# Dwarf Cleric
# Ability Name		Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type													Description																																																																																																																											Auto Feat								Caster level																Weapon prof. bonus			Source Page		Aspects
Smite Giants		KEY:Dwarf Cleric ~ Smite Giants		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Dwarf Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:A dwarf cleric who takes the 1st-level racial substitution level can attempt to smite a giant with a melee attack, similar to the way a paladin smites an evil creature. She adds her Constitution bonus (if any) to her attack roll and deals an extra 1 point of damage per cleric level. The cleric can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 1 + her Con modifier (minimum once per day). If the cleric accidentally smites a creature that is not a giant, the smite has no effect but still counts as one of the cleric's daily smite attempts. This substitution benefit replaces the standard cleric's ability to turn or rebuke undead.																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.146
Hammer Specialist		KEY:Dwarf Cleric ~ Hammer Specialist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Dwarf Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:A dwarf cleric's dedication to the forge-god results in exceptional skill with the warhammer. A dwarf cleric who takes the 4th-level racial substitution level gains the Martial Weapon Proficiency (warhammer) feat (if she doesn't already have it). She also gains a +2 bonus on damage rolls when wielding a warhammer in melee. This racial substitution level is only available to dwarf clerics who follow Moradin (or any other deity whose favored weapon is a warhammer). This benefit replaces the 2nd-level spell slot gained by a standard cleric at 4th level. From now on, the cleric can prepare one fewer 2nd-level cleric spell than indicated on Table 3-6, page 31 of the Player's Handbook.									ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Martial Weapon Proficiency (Warhammer)																			BONUS:WEAPONPROF=Warhammer|DAMAGE|2	SOURCEPAGE:p.146	ASPECT:CombatBonus|+2 bonus on damage rolls when wielding a warhammer in melee.
Earthen Spell Power	KEY:Dwarf Cleric ~ Earthen Spell Power	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Dwarf Cleric Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:A dwarf cleric who takes the 8th-level racial substitution level draws power from the earth when casting certain spells. When she is in contact with the ground, the cleric's effective caster level when casting spells with the earth descriptor (or any spell from the Earth domain, such as stoneskin) increases by one. This increase applies when determining level-dependent spell variables and on caster level checks. This increase stacks with other spell power abilities, such as from the hierophant prestige class. This benefit replaces the 4th-level spell slot gained by a standard cleric at 8th level. From now on, the cleric can prepare one fewer 4th-level cleric spell than indicated on Table 3-6, page 31 of the Player's Handbook.										BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Earth|1|TYPE=DwarfCleric	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DOMAIN.Earth|1|TYPE=DwarfCleric							SOURCEPAGE:p.146
